      "text": "The unspoken values of Agile are those values instrumental in making Agile work, that were implicitly assumed by early adopters. But when Agile crossed the chasm into the mainstream and the times and context changed, they got lost because they had not been codified and passed down. "
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "82afcc3529c2a6f1",
      "text": "There may be a connection between that and a few things that happened in the last 10 years, like\n- the appropriation, misinterpretation and stiffening of other's people work into commercial scaled frameworks\n- the unvetted misrepresentation of Agile by the big consultancy firms' canned solutions and standard recipes\n- and even some thought leader shifting their focus more toward the promotion of their own solution and less toward open collaboration as it used to be."
    },
